---

## ğŸ“¦ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/pet-api.git
cd pet-api
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Configure environment

Create a `.env` file in the root folder:

```env
Mongo_url=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/Pets
```

> Or use your MongoDB Atlas URI

### 4. Start the server

```bash
node index.js
```

---

## ğŸ“® API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint     | Description                     |
| ------ | ------------ | ------------------------------- |
| GET    | `/pet`       | List all pets or filter by type |
| GET    | `/pet/:name` | Get a pet by name               |
| POST   | `/pet`       | Add a new pet                   |
| PUT    | `/pet/:name` | Update a pet by name            |
| DELETE | `/pet/:name` | Delete a pet by name            |

### Sample POST Request

```json
{
  "name": "Buddy",
  "type": "Dog"
}
```

### Sample Filter Request

```
GET /pet?type=Cat
```

---

## ğŸ›  Error Responses

* `400 Bad Request` â€“ Missing fields or invalid input
* `404 Not Found` â€“ Pet not found
* `500 Internal Server Error` â€“ Database or server issues

